#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1400
#, no-c-format
msgid "All notifications can be edited here according to your preferences."
msgstr "Alle meldingen kunnen bewerkt worden volgens uw voorkeuren."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1409
#, no-c-format
msgid "Trouble Shooting"
msgstr "Problemen oplossen"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1416
#, no-c-format
msgid "Missing Programs"
msgstr "Ontbrekende programma's"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1418
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the system is missing some of the programs &smb4k; needs to operate "
"properly, it notifies the user:"
msgstr ""
"Als het systeem enkele van de programma's mist die &smb4k; nodig heeft om op "
"de juiste manier te werken, dan wordt dat aan de gebruiker gemeld:"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:1421
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the missing program notification"
msgstr "Schermafdruk van de melding over ontbrekend programma"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:1424
#, no-c-format
msgid "The missing program notification"
msgstr "De melding over ontbrekend programma"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1428
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this case, please install the specified program or, if it is already "
"present, add its location to the <envar>PATH</envar> environment variable in "
"your shell's configuration file (for the <ulink url=\"man:/bash"
"\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>bash</refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> shell it is the <filename>~/.bashrc</"
"filename> file)."
msgstr ""
"Installeer in dat geval het gespecificeerde programma of, als het al "
"aanwezig is, voeg zijn locatie toe aan de omgevingsvariabele <envar>PATH</"
"envar> aan het instellingenbestand van uw shell (voor de shell <ulink url="
"\"man:/bash\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>bash</refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> is dat het bestand <filename>~/.bashrc</"
"filename>)."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1436
#, no-c-format
msgid "Zeroconf Error"
msgstr "Zeroconf-fout"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1438
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&smb4k; uses the Zeroconf service (<application><ulink url=\"https://avahi."
"org\">Avahi</ulink></application>) to look up servers and shares in the "
"network neighborhood using DNS Service Discovery (DNS-SD). For this to work, "
"the Avahi daemon must be enabled and running on your system. If this is not "
"the case, &smb4k; shows an error message:"
msgstr ""
"&smb4k; gebruikt de Zeroconf-service (<application><ulink url=\"https://"
"avahi.org\">Avahi</ulink></application>) om servers en shares in de "
"netwerkomgeving op te zoeken met DNS Service Discovery (DNS-SD). Om dit te "
"laten werken moet de Avahi-daemon ingeschakeld en actief zijn op uw systeem. "
"Als dat niet het geval is zal &smb4k; een foutmelding tonen:"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:1441
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the Zeroconf error notification"
msgstr "Schermafdruk van de Zeroconf-foutmelding"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:1444
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Zeroconf error notification"
msgstr "De Zeroconf-foutmelding"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1448
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In most cases, the Avahi daemon is not running when an error is reported. "
"Under those &Linux; distributions that use <application>systemd</"
"application> you can start it by running the following or a similar command "
"from the terminal:"
msgstr ""
"In de meeste gevallen is de Avahi-daemon niet actief wanneer er een fout is "
"gerapporteerd. Onder de &Linux; distributies die <application>systemd</"
"application> gebruiken kunt u het starten met het volgende of gelijksoortige "
"commando vanaf de terminal:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:1449
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput><prompt>$</prompt> <command>sudo</command> <command>systemctl</"
"command> enable --now avahi-daemon</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput><prompt>$</prompt> <command>sudo</command> <command>systemctl</"
"command> enable --now avahi-daemon</userinput>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1450
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With all other &Linux; distributions and under BSD refer to the specific "
"documentation how to start the Avahi daemon."
msgstr ""
"Met alle andere &Linux; distributies en onder BSD bekijk de specifieke "
"documentatie over hoe de Avahi-daemon te starten."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1458
#, no-c-format
msgid "Denied Privilege Escalation"
msgstr "Geweigerde opschaling van rechten"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1460
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case the mount and unmount actions fail (most likely with an "
"<guilabel>AuthorizationDeniedError</guilabel> message), your polkit-1 setup "
"might need to be adjusted: Add a file, &eg; named <filename>10-mounthelper."
"rules</filename>, to the <filename class=\"directory\">$PREFIX/etc/polkit-1/"
"rules.d/</filename> directory with the following content:"
msgstr ""
"In het geval de acties aan- en afkoppelen mislukken met een bericht "
"<guilabel>AuthorizationDeniedError</guilabel>, dan zou uw polkit-1 opzet "
"aanpassing nodig kunnen hebben: Voeg een bestand toe, &eg; genaamd "
"<filename>10-mounthelper.rules</filename>, aan de map <filename class="
"\"directory\">$PREFIX/etc/polkit-1/rules.d/</filename> met de volgende "
"inhoud:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:1462
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"polkit.addRule(function(action, subject) {\n"
"        if (action.id == \"org.kde.smb4k.mounthelper.mount\" &amp;&amp; \n"
"            subject.isInGroup(\"wheel\")) {\n"
"                return polkit.Result.YES;\n"
"        }\n"
"});\n"
"\n"
"polkit.addRule(function(action, subject) {\n"
"        if (action.id == \"org.kde.smb4k.mounthelper.unmount\" &amp;&amp;\n"
"            subject.isInGroup(\"wheel\")) {\n"
"                return polkit.Result.YES;\n"
"        }\n"
"});"
msgstr ""
"polkit.addRule(function(action, subject) {\n"
"        if (action.id == \"org.kde.smb4k.mounthelper.mount\" &amp;&amp; \n"
"            subject.isInGroup(\"wheel\")) {\n"
"                return polkit.Result.YES;\n"
"        }\n"
"});\n"
"\n"
"polkit.addRule(function(action, subject) {\n"
"        if (action.id == \"org.kde.smb4k.mounthelper.unmount\" &amp;&amp;\n"
"            subject.isInGroup(\"wheel\")) {\n"
"                return polkit.Result.YES;\n"
"        }\n"
"});"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1464
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This allows all users in the Unix group <emphasis>wheel</emphasis> to "
"execute the mount and unmount actions. You may adjust the group of "
"authorized users to any group you prefer to use (&eg; <emphasis>sudo</"
"emphasis> or <emphasis>operator</emphasis>)."
msgstr ""
"Dit stelt alle gebruikers in de Unix-groep <emphasis>wheel</emphasis> in "
"staat om de acties aan- en afkoppelen uit te voeren. U kunt de groep van "
"geautoriseerde gebruikers aanpassen tot elke groep die u wenst (&eg; "
"<emphasis>sudo</emphasis> of <emphasis>operator</emphasis>)."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1472
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mounting Problems Under BSD"
msgstr "Problemen met aankoppelen onder BSD"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1474
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If mounting of shares from either a &Samba; or a &Windows; server fails, "
"this might be because <ulink url=\"man:/mount_smbfs"
"\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount_smbfs</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> only uses NTLMv1 authentication and "
"requires the SMB 1.0/&CIFS; protocol, and the server does not support those. "
"To fix mounting for a &Samba; server, you can add the following entries to "
"the [global] section of the <ulink url=\"man:/smb.conf"
"\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle><filename>smb.conf</filename></"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>5</manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> file of "
"<emphasis>the server</emphasis>:"
msgstr ""
"Als aankoppelen van shares ofwel vanaf een &Samba; of een &Windows; server "
"mislukt, dan kan dat zijn omdat <ulink url=\"man:/mount_smbfs"
"\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount_smbfs</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> alleen authenticatie met NTLMv1 gebruikt "
"en het SMB 1.0/&CIFS;-protocol vereist en de server die niet ondersteunt. Om "
"aankoppelen voor een &Samba; server te repareren, kunt u de volgende items "
"toevoegen aan de sectie [global] van het bestand <ulink url=\"man:/smb.conf"
"\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle><filename>smb.conf</filename></"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>5</manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> van "
"<emphasis>de server</emphasis>:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:1476
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"[global]\n"
"...\n"
"ntlm auth = yes\n"
"server min protocol = NT1\n"
"..."
msgstr ""
"[global]\n"
"...\n"
"ntlm auth = yes\n"
"server min protocol = NT1\n"
"..."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1478
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to fix this issue for a &Windows; server, please contact the "
"sysadmin and tell her or him that NTLMv1 authentication and the SMB 1.0/"
"&CIFS; protocol should be switched on (if possible)."
msgstr ""
"Als u dit probleem voor een &Windows;-server wilt repareren, neemt u contact "
"op met de systeembeheerder en vertelt u haar of hem dat NTLMv1 authenticatie "
"en het SMB 1.0/&CIFS;-protocol ingeschakeld zou moeten worden (indien "
"mogelijk)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1480
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is not advisable to enable the SMB 1.0/&CIFS; protocol on a server, "
"because it is considered insecure (see &eg; <ulink url=\"https://"
"techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/storage-at-microsoft/stop-using-smb1/ba-"
"p/425858\">here</ulink>) and was thus disabled in newer &Samba; and "
"&Windows; versions (see &eg; <ulink url=\"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/"
"archive/blogs/josebda/the-deprecation-of-smb1-you-should-be-planning-to-get-"
"rid-of-this-old-smb-dialect\">here</ulink> and <ulink url=\"https://www."
"samba.org/samba/history/samba-4.11.0.html\">here</ulink>)."
msgstr ""
"Het is niet aan te raden om het SMB 1.0/&CIFS;-protocol op een server in te "
"schakelen, omdat het als onveilig wordt gezien (zie &eg; <ulink url="
"\"https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/storage-at-microsoft/stop-using-"
"smb1/ba-p/425858\">here</ulink>) en was dus uitgeschakeld in nieuwer &Samba; "
"en &Windows; versies (zie &eg; <ulink url=\"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-"
"us/archive/blogs/josebda/the-deprecation-of-smb1-you-should-be-planning-to-"
"get-rid-of-this-old-smb-dialect\">hier</ulink> en <ulink url=\"https://www."
"samba.org/samba/history/samba-4.11.0.html\">hier</ulink>)."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1488
#, no-c-format
msgid "Other Desktop Environments Than &plasma;"
msgstr "Andere Bureaubladomgevingen dan &plasma;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1490
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When using a different desktop environment than &plasma;, &Qt; and &kde-"
"frameworks; applications might be missing some icons. In that case, you "
"might want to install the <application>qt6ct</application> (<ulink url="
"\"https://github.com/trialuser02/qt6ct\">download</ulink>) application. To "
"use it with your desktop environment, add the following to your <filename>~/."
"xinitrc</filename> or <filename>~/.profile</filename> file:"
msgstr ""
"Bij gebruik van een andere bureaubladomgeving dan &plasma;, &Qt; en &kde-"
"frameworks; kunnen toepassingen sommige pictogrammen ontbreken. In dat geval "
"kunt u de toepassing <application>qt6ct</application> (<ulink url=\"https://"
"github.com/trialuser02/qt6ct\">downloaden</ulink>). Om het met uw "
"bureaubladomgeving te gebruiken, voeg het volgende toe aan uw bestand "
"<filename>~/.xinitrc</filename> of <filename>~/.profile</filename>:"

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:1491
#, no-c-format
msgid "X11:"
msgstr "X11:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:1492
#, no-c-format
msgid "export QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME=qt6ct"
msgstr "export QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME=qt6ct"

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:1493
#, no-c-format
msgid "Wayland:"
msgstr "Wayland:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:1494
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"export QT_QPA_PLATFORM=wayland\n"
"export QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME=qt6ct"
msgstr ""
"export QT_QPA_PLATFORM=wayland\n"
"export QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME=qt6ct"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1505
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring &smb4k;"
msgstr "&smb4k; instellen"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1507
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section describes the settings that can be used to configure &smb4k;. "
"To open the configuration dialog, you must click the <link linkend="
"\"mainwindow_overview\"><guimenuitem>Configure &smb4k;...</guimenuitem></"
"link> menu item."
msgstr ""
"Deze sectie beschrijft de instellingen die gebruikt kunnen worden om &smb4k; "
"te configureren. Om de configuratiedialoog te openen klikt u op het menu-"
"item <link linkend=\"mainwindow_overview\"><guimenuitem>&smb4k; "
"configureren...</guimenuitem></link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1514
#, no-c-format
msgid "User Interface"
msgstr "Gebruikersinterface"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1516
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can change the appearance and behavior of several dialogs and widgets "
"with the options located here. Please note that if you want to change the "
"appearance of the main window, additional options are available under "
"<guimenu>Settings</guimenu> in the <link linkend=\"mainwindow_overview"
"\">menu bar</link>."
msgstr ""
"U kunt het uiterlijk en het gedrag van verschillende dialogen en widgets met "
"de hier aanwezige opties wijzigen. Merk op dat als u het uiterlijk van het "
"hoofdvenster wilt wijzigen, u deze aanwezig zijn in de <link linkend="
"\"mainwindow_overview\">menubalk</link> onder <guimenu>Instellingen</"
"guimenu>."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:1518
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the \"User Interface\" configuration tab"
msgstr "Schermafdruk van het tabblad voor instellingen \"Gebruikersinterface\""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:1521
#, no-c-format
msgid "The \"Appearance\" configuration tab"
msgstr "Het instellingentabblad voor \"Uiterlijk\""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1529
#, no-c-format
msgid "Main Window"
msgstr "Hoofdvenster"

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:1534
#, no-c-format
msgid "Tab orientation"
msgstr "Oriëntatie van tabblad"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1537
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Define the location of the tabs if the dock widgets in the main window are "
"arranged as tabs. The following values can be chosen:"
